<br>
Uber guilds -- yes, if they need an epic drop, they'll pop in to the guild and dominate.  But the thing is -- they don't go INTO the planes except for epic drops.  I really seriously don't think there's anything that would prevent people from being able to hit the planes during FFA periods if you have some flexibility.<br>
<br>
Your comment about 100 guilds and only one public event -- maybe a survey of how many unguilded people there are who are interested in planar raids and would attend public events would be useful.  If that number is 100, then it's reasonable to ask for more public events.  If it's 10, then it's unreasonable.<br>
<br>
For all practical purposes, you are the ONLY person who is complaining.  Where are these hordes of unguilded people who need these public events?<br>
<br>
And you NEVER asked to host an event.  You whined.  There's a huge difference.<br>
<br>
Personally, I'm not impressed with Flewl's entry.  It's contrary to the summit discussion that was held.  I personally don't have any problem at all if you find a date you'd like in Feb or early March.  Because he STILL hasn't posted a roster -- just a set of rules -- I'm quite ready to yank his post.  I'll be emailing him....<br>
<br>
I'm also going to be checking how how he posted a public event in the first place.  I thought I prevented that.<br>
<br>
But GDI, Rumenia, how about TRYING to be nice instead of constantly complaining?  Why not assume, just once, that honey works better than a flame thrower?<br>
